<title>UK: UK's Clarke says sales data in line with forecasts.</title>
<headline>UK's Clarke says sales data in line with forecasts.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-12-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Britain's Chancellor of the Exchequer Kenneth Clarke said Wednesday's unemployment and retail sales figures confirmed Britain's economic prospects were the &quot;best for a generation.&quot;</p>
<p>Clarke told a news conference that consumers were &quot;spending with confidence.&quot; He called the rise in retail sales &quot;very good&quot; but said it was in line with government forecasts.</p>
<p>Clarke, recalling that he raised interest rates by a quarter-point in October and produced what he called a tight budget in November, said he was &quot;conscious of the need&quot; to keep the economic recovery on a steady course.</p>
<p>-- Alan Wheatley, London newsroom +44 171 542 2774</p>
